We need to reinvigorate the United States industrial base to produce generic medicines and antibiotics domestically. Doing so will create thousands of new middle-class jobs and make our country safer.

The Chinese government is the principal developer of generic prescriptions, which account for approximately 90 percent of pharmaceuticals. China’s chokehold on the global pharmaceutical market leaves our servicemembers and our nation vulnerable to attack.
Right now, China has the ability to attack the United States without firing a single shot by poisoning our servicemembers’ medicines or cutting off their supply.
